gomodel:SYNGO_4138  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: By ultrastructure studies, authors find that the absence of p75NTR results in a significant reduction in the number of synaptic vesicles and active zones, as well as in the density of the readily releasable pool (RRP) of vesicles.\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada:\nThe paper shows that p75NTR KO leads to a reduction in the number of SV/AZ/RRPs, however, simply based on ultrastructural data, it is difficult to attribute the consequence of this on synaptic BP. Hence, a generic term \"presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission\" was chosen.. Experimental description: The C57BL/6 J strain B6.129S4-Ngfrtm1Jae/J p75NTR-/- mice and their control pairs were purchased from The Jackson Laboratory (Sacramento, California, USA)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9888-0928" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2345-393X" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4138" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

